The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 25 August is 65,734 (7,576.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 20 August, there were 2,671 new confirmed cases (307.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 13 August, there were 2,540 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 5% (131 extra cases).
